Create a Named Credential for Query Workspaces

Add a named credential using auth provider information to create a secure connection in Data Cloud. A named credential specifies the URL of a callout endpoint and its required authentication parameters. You can create multiple named credentials to connect to different orgs in Data Cloud.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSION SET NEEDED
To create a named credential:	Data Cloud Admin
From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Named Credentials, and select Named Credentials.
From the New dropdown, select New Legacy.
Enter the label, name, and host URL. For the host URL enter https://<<orgdomain>>.my.salesforce.com/ and substitute <<orgdomain>> with the domain name of your org.
For Identity Type, select Named Principal.
For Authentication Protocol, select OAuth 2.0.
For Authentication Provider, select the auth provider that you created in Create an Auth Provider for Query Workspaces step.
For Scope, enter api web refresh_token cdp_query_api.
Select Start Authentication Flow on Save.
Select Allow Merge Fields in HTTP Header.
Select Allow Merge Fields in HTTP Body.
Click Save.
Syncing the named credential can take up to 5 minutes.
